346
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:07,000
نحن مجرد طبيب ومريض!

347
00:37:07,440 --> 00:37:09,760
نحن لا نتواعد. [[ن]] حقا؟ [[ن]] لكن قلادة الطبيب
يكون حول رقبة المريض.

348
00:37:13,480 --> 00:37:14,480
من الأفضل أن تشتري لي البيرة بعد ذلك. [[ن]] بخير. سأشتري لك مصنعًا كاملاً. [[ن]] مثالي. الآن، أنا متحمس.

349
00:37:15,040 --> 00:37:16,200
استمر في تلقي الأوامر.

350
00:37:18,640 --> 00:37:20,840
أوه، هذه الموسيقى ليست مناسبة تمامًا.

351
00:37:25,320 --> 00:37:26,720
- هذا أفضل .
- انسخ ذلك.

352
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:31,040
الوقت يطير حقًا، أليس كذلك؟

353
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:37,080
يبدو الأمر كما لو كان بالأمس فقط
كنا جميعًا نتناول العشاء معًا.

354
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:42,040
هذا صحيح يا أمي.

355
00:37:44,600 --> 00:37:45,640
هل تتذكر ما قاله لك والدك؟

356
00:37:46,086 --> 00:37:48,406
بغض النظر عما يحدث،

357
00:37:51,640 --> 00:37:52,640
أحبوا بعضكم البعض.

358
00:37:53,200 --> 00:37:54,840
لأن العائلة

359
00:38:00,200 --> 00:38:01,520
هي أهم شيء.

360
00:38:05,440 --> 00:38:06,440
نحن نتذكر يا أمي.

361
00:38:11,760 --> 00:38:14,000
لكننا ما زلنا نتقاتل طوال الوقت. [[ن]] يحدث ذلك. [[ن]] أعلم.

362
00:38:14,040 --> 00:38:16,040
يمكنكم القتال، ولكن بمجرد الانتهاء،

363
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:17,999
يسامحون بعضكم البعض دائمًا.

364
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:21,320
أفتقد أبي.

365
00:38:21,640 --> 00:38:23,280
أنا أفتقده أيضًا.

366
00:38:32,160 --> 00:38:33,400
إذًا، ما هو العشاء الليلة؟

367
00:38:35,040 --> 00:38:36,640
حفلة شواء للمأكولات البحرية على الشاطئ؟

368
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:39,760
هل يمكنني... أن أدعو أصدقائي؟

369
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:42,640
إذا قمت بذلك، فأنا أدعو عائلتي أيضًا. [[ن]] جيد. سأدعو الأطفال
من المتجر للانضمام إلينا.

370
00:38:42,680 --> 00:38:44,079
مع من تعيش هنا؟

371
00:38:44,080 --> 00:38:45,080
حسنًا...

372
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:47,679
انفصل والداي عندما كنت طفلاً.

373
00:38:47,680 --> 00:38:51,280
وفي ذلك الوقت،
اخترت البقاء مع أمي.

374
00:38:51,400 --> 00:38:52,960
ربما لا يزال والدي غاضبًا مني

375
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:54,599
لأنني لم أختره.

376
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:57,680
الحقيقة هي...

377
00:39:04,120 --> 00:39:05,400
لم أرغب أبدًا في الاختيار على الإطلاق.

378
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:06,880
لأنه بغض النظر عمن اخترته...

379
00:39:11,520 --> 00:39:13,080
سأظل أنا المخطئ.

380
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:17,320
(الحلقة القادمة)
لم يكن لدي صديق قط.

381
00:39:20,720 --> 00:39:22,960
ثم... أعطني قبلة.

382
00:39:28,120 --> 00:39:30,400
مضيف وعميل.
هل هذا ممكن حقا؟

383
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:39,720
خذ هذا المنزل، لذلك
يمكن للجدة تناول وجبة دافئة. [[ن]] الجدة؟! الجدة!

384
00:39:42,200 --> 00:39:43,920
جدتك ستكون بخير.

385
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:00,640
أريد أن أرى Nabnueng.

386
00:40:03,440 --> 00:40:05,320
لقد مر وقت طويل يا بني. [[ن]] لا! [[ن]] سيلوم! [[ن]]

387
00:40:21,360 --> 00:40:22,520
I'm sorry.

388
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:25,800
I'm… so sorry, P'Doc.

389
00:40:27,760 --> 00:40:29,880
You don't have to apologize.

390
00:40:30,320 --> 00:40:32,160
You did nothing wrong.

391
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:39,640
I'm right here with you.

392
00:40:54,240 --> 00:40:55,840
Hey, Sailom.

393
00:40:56,080 --> 00:40:58,880
Are you still stressing about
what happened at the bike trip?

394
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:00,759
Of course I am.

395
00:41:00,760 --> 00:41:03,280
I totally ruined his trip.

396
00:41:03,720 --> 00:41:05,999
Ruined it how? Everything went fine.

397
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:07,640
Everyone made it back home safely.

398
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:09,040
Nobody got hurt.

399
00:41:09,720 --> 00:41:12,080
But they were all shocked because of me.

400
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:14,200
If it wasn't for my condition,

401
00:41:15,440 --> 00:41:17,720
P'Doc's trip
wouldn't have been so disrupted.

402
00:41:18,920 --> 00:41:20,840
You're overthinking it.

403
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:22,920
P'Doc didn't even say a word about it.

404
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:25,360
Or maybe he did,
but we didn't know?

405
00:41:25,440 --> 00:41:28,600
If your mouth is so free,
just stuff it with this!

406
00:41:29,400 --> 00:41:30,520
Damn you!

407
00:41:33,240 --> 00:41:35,880
Ugh! What am I going to do?!

408
00:41:38,840 --> 00:41:41,040
- Thank you for coming.
- Yes.

409
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:42,240
Thank you.

410
00:41:45,200 --> 00:41:46,720
What can I get for you?

411
00:41:46,800 --> 00:41:49,520
A cheesecake and a Thai tea, please.

412
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:51,880
A cheesecake and a Thai tea… and?

413
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:54,199
- A pink milk, please.
- Got it.

414
00:41:54,224 --> 00:41:55,944
Wow, we're really busy today.

415
00:41:56,840 --> 00:41:59,840
It's been non-stop
since the bike trip ended.

416
00:42:00,280 --> 00:42:02,640
Oh, please help make some more desserts.

417
00:42:02,680 --> 00:42:05,480
Sure thing. As soon as I
finish making this cup.

418
00:42:05,600 --> 00:42:07,000
- Thank you.
- Of course.

419
00:42:10,680 --> 00:42:14,000
Does the chain come off
when you're picking up speed?

420
00:42:15,760 --> 00:42:19,439
I think it's an issue with the gears.
Please have a seat and wait.

421
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:20,520
Thank you.

422
00:42:24,720 --> 00:42:26,359
You can wait over here.

423
00:42:26,360 --> 00:42:28,439
Or if you'd like some coffee,

424
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:29,840
we have a café over there.

425
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:32,040
I think I'll wait at the café.

426
00:42:32,080 --> 00:42:33,600
Certainly. Right this way.

427
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:47,080
How long will you stand there?

428
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:48,800
Help me fix these.

429
00:42:52,040 --> 00:42:54,679
Stop posing already. Hurry up.

430
00:42:54,680 --> 00:42:55,720
Fine.

431
00:42:56,080 --> 00:42:57,560
Help me take this wheel off.

432
00:42:59,320 --> 00:43:00,560
Hey, Tawan!

433
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:03,640
Can you edit a clip for our page?

434
00:43:03,960 --> 00:43:06,200
Look at all these bikes around you.

435
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:12,880
Ever since your bike trip ended,

436
00:43:13,640 --> 00:43:16,040
the shop's been flooded!

437
00:43:18,480 --> 00:43:20,319
Forget about editing clips.

438
00:43:20,320 --> 00:43:22,400
I don't even have time to breathe.

439
00:43:25,160 --> 00:43:26,040
By the way,

440
00:43:26,041 --> 00:43:27,680
how's that kid doing?

441
00:43:28,040 --> 00:43:29,040
Which kid?

442
00:43:29,760 --> 00:43:31,400
The kid who freaked out.

443
00:43:33,486 --> 00:43:35,246
Oh, you mean Sailom?

444
00:43:36,840 --> 00:43:38,759
You saw it yourself.

445
00:43:38,760 --> 00:43:40,280
He can't be touched.

446
00:43:40,560 --> 00:43:44,760
Is this the patient
you told me and Sky about that time?

447
00:43:45,480 --> 00:43:46,480
Yep.

448
00:43:47,800 --> 00:43:48,920
That's a tough one.

449
00:43:49,520 --> 00:43:50,720
Good luck with that.

450
00:44:02,800 --> 00:44:04,440
How many more bikes are left?

451
00:44:06,680 --> 00:44:12,200
Give it a try in the next couple of
days. It should be working fine now.

452
00:44:12,473 --> 00:44:15,233
I just had the mechanic
double-check and test everything.

453
00:44:16,480 --> 00:44:17,880
Thank you so much.

454
00:44:17,920 --> 00:44:22,360
If you run into any more issues,
just let us know. We're happy to help.

455
00:44:22,480 --> 00:44:23,920
Yes, thank you.

456
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:25,040
You're welcome.

457
00:44:29,320 --> 00:44:30,320
Sailom?

458
00:44:43,080 --> 00:44:44,960
You're here to see me, right?

459
00:44:50,960 --> 00:44:53,480
If there's anything you want to say,

460
00:44:53,560 --> 00:44:54,840
I'm listening.

461
00:44:58,320 --> 00:45:01,600
I'm so sorry for ruining your trip.

462
00:45:03,240 --> 00:45:05,200
I really didn't mean it.

463
00:45:05,240 --> 00:45:07,000
Please don't be mad at me.

464
00:45:08,480 --> 00:45:11,200
If there's anything I can do to help,

465
00:45:11,600 --> 00:45:13,000
please tell me.

466
00:45:13,720 --> 00:45:16,040
I don't want to feel guilty anymore.

467
00:45:18,200 --> 00:45:20,520
You didn't do anything wrong.

468
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:25,000
If you're worried that I'm angry,

469
00:45:25,560 --> 00:45:28,560
don't be. I'm not mad at all.

470
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:31,000
I actually understand.

471
00:45:33,720 --> 00:45:34,840
Really?

472
00:45:36,240 --> 00:45:37,320
Really.

473
00:45:42,400 --> 00:45:45,440
I actually am looking for some help.

474
00:45:46,760 --> 00:45:48,120
Know how to edit videos?

475
00:45:49,040 --> 00:45:51,320
- Edit videos?
- Yes.

476
00:45:52,240 --> 00:45:55,200
I need someone to edit
the bike trip clips for our page.

477
00:45:55,920 --> 00:45:57,160
Can you do that?

478
00:45:58,880 --> 00:46:00,760
Yes! I can do that!

479
00:46:07,400 --> 00:46:08,400
Hurry up!

480
00:46:08,480 --> 00:46:09,960
Yeah, I'm on it.

481
00:46:10,920 --> 00:46:13,040
Wait! Keep this part.

482
00:46:13,080 --> 00:46:14,280
This shot is beautiful.

483
00:46:14,640 --> 00:46:15,960
Put this clip right here!

484
00:46:16,000 --> 00:46:17,000
Geez.

485
00:46:17,480 --> 00:46:19,640
Why don't you do it yourself?

486
00:46:21,120 --> 00:46:23,080
Here's the mouse.

487
00:46:27,160 --> 00:46:28,360
Please, continue.

488
00:46:29,560 --> 00:46:32,360
I promise I'll be quiet.

489
00:46:32,400 --> 00:46:34,400
Not a peep from me.

490
00:46:34,680 --> 00:46:36,920
If you can't even edit,
why did you volunteer?

491
00:46:38,320 --> 00:46:41,320
P'Doc couldn't find anyone to help.

492
00:46:41,680 --> 00:46:45,079
I must do anything
I can do to help him. Right?

493
00:46:45,080 --> 00:46:46,880
Want to help your boyfriend, huh?

494
00:46:47,120 --> 00:46:48,280
Come on!

495
00:46:48,440 --> 00:46:50,720
We're just doctor and patient!

496
00:46:51,240 --> 00:46:52,840
We're not dating.

497
00:46:53,520 --> 00:46:54,880
Really?

498
00:46:56,080 --> 00:46:59,280
But the doctor's necklace
is around the patient's neck.

499
00:47:08,280 --> 00:47:10,320
You better buy me beers after this.

500
00:47:11,240 --> 00:47:14,279
Fine. I'll buy you a whole factory.

501
00:47:14,280 --> 00:47:16,160
Perfect. Now, I'm motivated.

502
00:47:17,320 --> 00:47:18,840
Keep the orders coming.

503
00:47:21,200 --> 00:47:23,720
Oh, this music isn't quite right.

504
00:47:24,120 --> 00:47:26,320
- This one is better.
- Copy that.

505
00:47:40,640 --> 00:47:42,440
Time really flies, doesn't it?

506
00:47:42,920 --> 00:47:47,280
It feels like just yesterday
we were all having dinner together.

507
00:47:47,600 --> 00:47:48,920
It really does, Mom.

508
00:47:50,040 --> 00:47:53,280
Remember what your dad told you?

509
00:47:53,760 --> 00:47:55,680
No matter what happens,

510
00:47:55,960 --> 00:47:57,800
love one another.

511
00:47:58,080 --> 00:47:59,560
Because family

512
00:47:59,600 --> 00:48:01,280
is the most important thing.

513
00:48:02,560 --> 00:48:03,640
We remember, Mom.

514
00:48:04,320 --> 00:48:06,400
But we still fight all the time.

515
00:48:07,520 --> 00:48:08,920
It happens.

516
00:48:09,320 --> 00:48:10,600
I know.

517
00:48:10,760 --> 00:48:13,440
You can fight, but once it's over,

518
00:48:13,480 --> 00:48:15,320
always forgive each other.

519
00:48:16,200 --> 00:48:18,080
I miss Dad.

520
00:48:19,680 --> 00:48:21,800
I miss him too.

521
00:48:25,240 --> 00:48:27,080
So, what's for dinner tonight?

522
00:48:29,080 --> 00:48:30,880
A seafood BBQ by the beach?

523
00:48:31,640 --> 00:48:34,400
Can… I invite my friends over?

524
00:48:36,400 --> 00:48:38,080
If you do, I'm inviting mine too.

525
00:48:38,360 --> 00:48:41,600
Good. I'll invite the kids
from the shop to join us.

526
00:49:18,520 --> 00:49:20,120
Who do you live here with?

527
00:49:27,560 --> 00:49:28,560
Well...

528
00:49:30,280 --> 00:49:33,680
my parents split up when I was a kid.

529
00:49:35,520 --> 00:49:37,800
And back then,
I chose to stay with my mom.

530
00:49:38,800 --> 00:49:41,000
Maybe my dad is still mad at me

531
00:49:41,520 --> 00:49:43,320
because I didn't choose him.

532
00:49:45,040 --> 00:49:46,439
The truth is...

533
00:49:46,440 --> 00:49:48,520
I never wanted to choose at all.

534
00:49:51,400 --> 00:49:53,360
Because no matter who I chose...

535
00:49:54,680 --> 00:49:56,840
I would still be the one at fault.

536
00:50:11,280 --> 00:50:12,720
(Next Episode)
Never had a boyfriend.

537
00:50:12,840 --> 00:50:14,480
Then... give me a kiss.

538
00:50:15,400 --> 00:50:18,960
A host and a customer.
Is it really possible?

539
00:50:19,840 --> 00:50:22,800
Take this home, so your
grandma can have a warm meal.

540
00:50:23,720 --> 00:50:26,000
Grandma?! Grandma!

541
00:50:26,360 --> 00:50:28,480
Your grandma is going to be okay.

542
00:50:30,040 --> 00:50:31,880
I want to see Nabnueng.

543
00:50:33,360 --> 00:50:35,200
It's been a long time, son.

544
00:50:38,440 --> 00:50:39,440
NO!

545
00:50:39,520 --> 00:50:40,520
Sailom!

